{
  "texts": [
    "The escalating use of AI techniques has propelled the development of novel adaptive and intelligent systems tailored for educational purposes, fostering notable parallels between CBE and AI in education [47,52,55].",
    "Learning management systems [5] serve as a prime example of this convergence.",
    "Test and quiz systems, integral components of CBE, have also undergone significant transformations, with contemporary implementations reflecting the fusion of AI methodologies [53,56].Digitalization in education typically involves the adoption of digital tools and technologies for teaching, learning, and administrative purposes to enhance traditional educational practices [54].",
    "AI in education goes beyond simple digitalization by leveraging AI algorithms and techniques such as machine learning, natural language processing, Fig. 1 Core domains of artificial intelligence applications in educational contexts [36,37] Discover Artificial Intelligence (2024) 4:110 | https://doi.org/10.1007/s44163-024-00163-y Review and predictive analytics to provide personalized learning experiences, adaptive feedback, and data-driven insights for educators and students [52].",
    "AI in education refers to the integration of AI technologies to improve educational processes, adapt learning experiences to individual students' needs, streamline administrative tasks, and enhance overall learning outcomes through automation, personalization, and data-driven insights [6].In AI, Learning Analytics (LA) represents the intricate process of collecting, analyzing, and reporting data related to learners and their learning environments [6], aiming to comprehend and optimize the learning experience and its contexts [50]."
  ]
}